ta, Ling follows the trajectories of dozens of children coming of age at a time of competing economic and social imperatives, and its everyday ramifications on their sense of identity, educational outcomes, and citizenship claims. Under policies and practices of segmented inclusion, they are inevitably funneled through the school system toward a life of manual labor. Illuminating the aspirations and strategies of these young men and women, Ling captures their experiences against the backdrop of a reemergent global Shanghai.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aChildren of internal migrantszChinazShanghaixSocial conditions. 0aRural-urban migrationxSocial aspectszChinazShanghai. 0aYouthzChinazShanghaixSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aChina.  acitizenship.  ainequality.  alate-socialism.  amigration.  aschool-to-work transition.  asegmented inclusion.  asocial reproduction.  aurban governance.  aurbanization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361077440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503610774423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503610774.jpg  a978-3-11-069218-1  SUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK 